      y = x**2
      plot(x,y,label="$y=x^2$")
      xlabel('x')
      ylabel('y')
      title('Graph of $y=x^2$')
      legend()
      show()
      . . .
      In [33]:

      x = linspace(0,5)
      y = x**2

      xlabel('x-Axis')
      ylabel('y-Axis')
      title('Graph of $y =x^2$')
      legend(loc=3)
      show()

      f = np.sin(x)
      g = np.cos(x)
      plot(x,f,label="sin x")
      plot(x,g,label="cos x")
      xlabel('x')
      ylabel('y')
      title('Graph of $f(x) = sinx & g(x) = cosx$')
      legend()
      show()

      Subplots

      Subplots

      In [4]:
      xxxxxxxxxx
       
      #Plot the Graph of sinx ,cosx, e^x and x^2 in [0,5 ] in one figure with 2 X  2 Subplots
      . . .
      In [8]:
      xxxxxxxxxx
       
      x = np.linspace(0,5)
      y1 = np.sin(x)
      y2 = np.cos(x)
      y3 = np.exp(x)
      y4 = x**2
      subplot(2,2,1)
      plot(x,y1,label= "$sinx$")
      legend()
      subplot(2,2,2)
      plot(x,y2,label= "$cosx$")
      legend()
      subplot(2,2,3)
      plot(x,y3,label= "$e^x$")
      legend()
      subplot(2,2,4)
      plot(x,y4,label= "$x^2$")
      legend()
      show()
      . . .
      In [28]:
      xxxxxxxxxx
       
      x = np.linspace(1,5)
      y1 = np.exp(x)
      y2 = np.exp(-x)
      y3 = np.exp(1/x)
      subplot(3,1,1)
      plot(x,y1,'m',ls= '-.',label= "$e^x$")
      legend(loc=1)
      subplot(3,1,2)
      plot(x,y2,'g',ls= ':',label= "$e^-x$")
      legend()
      subplot(3,1,3)
      plot(x,y3,'k',ls= '--',label= "$e^1/x$")
      legend()
      show()
      . . .
